<br>
  If our ability to take hits is going to be reduced, then AC doesn't matter as much as it used to on items.<br>
<br>
 Hence, HP takes a huge boost in it's relevance, and it was already my top stat.<br>
<br>
  Hence, the regen on the Fungi Tunic, given that we're going to be hit anyways, is going to be of a benefit ASSUMING that we last longer than X between heals, where X is the number of ticks it'd take us to regen the HP we loose by going with a Fungi.<br>
<br>
  Lets take an Icicle Tunic for example.  If grouped, and you're being healed for arguments dake by CH, then you need to last roughly 4 ticks between CH's to regen the 80 HP an Icicle Tunic gives you.<br>
<br>
  It's still as useful as it ever was.  More so in my opinion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wubao>Wubao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Posts: 1630<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/10/02 9:27:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11803.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> heh</span><hr size=1> &quot;Hence, the regen on the Fungi Tunic, given that we're going to be hit anyways, is going to be of a benefit &quot;<br>
